What is state of california fm?

The state of california fm is a financial form used for reporting income and expenses in the state of California.

Who is required to file state of california fm?

Individuals and businesses who earn income in the state of California are required to file state of california fm.

How to fill out state of california fm?

You can fill out the state of california fm either manually or electronically through the California Franchise Tax Board website.

What is the purpose of state of california fm?

The purpose of state of california fm is to report income, deductions, and credits to calculate the tax liability for individuals and businesses in California.

What information must be reported on state of california fm?

Income, deductions, credits, and other financial information must be reported on state of california fm.

When is the deadline to file state of california fm in 2023?

The deadline to file state of california fm in 2023 is April 15th.

What is the penalty for the late filing of state of california fm?

The penalty for late filing of state of california fm is 5% of the unpaid tax amount per month, up to a maximum of 25%.
